{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Appoint a separate Minister for Leasehold.",
        "additional_details": "In the aftermath of the Grenfell tragedy, it is right that many buildings require fire safety improvements. However, the way in which this is currently being implemented exposes Leaseholders to the risk of financial abuse. \r\n\r\nIt is clear from recent consultation with regards to the Building Safety Bill that one Minister cannot advocate on behalf of Leaseholders at the same time as Freeholders and the Construction Industry. \r\n\r\nWe are calling for a separate Minister for Leasehold to be appointed.",
        "background": "At present there is Minister of State for Building Safety, Leasehold and Communities. \r\n\r\nThe Minister of State cannot act in the best interests of Leaseholders at the same time as Freeholders. As such, there should be an independent Minister for Leasehold appointed.",
        "closed_at": "2021-06-01T22:59:59.999Z",
